'''Abib''', ''[[noun (part of speech)|noun]]'' [Heb. ''ab&imacr;b'', lit. an ear of corn. The month was so called from barley being at that time in ear.]

The first month of the Jewish ecclesiastical year, corresponding nearly to our [[April]]. After the [[Babylonish]] [[captivity]] this month was called ''Nisan''. ''[[Kitto (source)|Kitto]].''